In this phase, the main contradiction is identified in terms of controllable and measurable variables.
Definitions:
CONTROL PARAMETER (CP): physical or operational variable directly modifiable in the system
EVALUATION PARAMETER 1 (EP1): performance to be improved
EVALUATION PARAMETER 2 (EP2): performance that worsens when EP1 improves
The contradiction emerges from system behavior when varying the CONTROL PARAMETER:
If CP increases → EP1 improves but EP2 worsens
If CP decreases → EP2 improves but EP1 worsens
(For the hairdryer:
CONTROL PARAMETER
Effective surface energy of the hair-skin system, i.e., wettability of the surface.
EVALUATION PARAMETER 1
Water removal speed from the surface.
EVALUATION PARAMETER 2
Energy consumption of the system.
CONTRADICTION
If the parameter is increased, water removal speed increases but energy consumption also increases. If it is decreased, energy consumption decreases but water removal speed also decreases.)
